        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 6:28PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
extending near Hardin moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, half inch size hail and torrential
rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hardin, Crow Agency, Busby, Crow Indian Reservation and Northern
Cheyenne Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
